content.description: Climb up the middle of the face, via a shallow groove, on small edges and friction. Move left on a shelf and surmount the bulge above on friction, to a set of deep pockets. Continue up the face following the line of pockets. Climb through the large pocket and to the top on knobs and inclusions.
content.location: Center line on the north face.

content.description: Begin climbing up the crack formed by a large partially detached block, and move right at its top. Continue up the edge of the rounded buttress on incuts, knobs, and the occasional  pocket. Near the top, features diminish and small depressions, edges, and fiction lead to the anchor.
content.location: The right-most line on the face. Just left of the undercut base of the Briscoe County Boulder and the arÃªte.

content.description: Friction up the slab and move left after clipping the 2nd bolt. After traversing left continue up the face below a bulge. Pull the bulge and continue to the top on incuts and knobs. As the name implies there isn't much in the way of pockets on this line.
content.location: Left-most line on the north face of Briscoe County Boulder.

climbs.name: Eating Mangoes on a Nude Beach

content.description: Climbs the left arete thru a small bulge at the top to the anchor. Crux at the bottom.
content.location: Left most route, on the arete
